<%= lato_page_head "Documentation" %>

<h2>How to use Lato Settings</h2>

<p>
  <code>lato_settings</code> is Rails engine for managing application settings inside Lato admin.
  It provides CRUD UI for settings and helper methods to read typed values from application code.
</p>

<h3>Installation</h3>

<p>Add Lato and Lato Settings to application Gemfile:</p>

<pre><code>gem "lato"
gem "lato_settings"</code></pre>

<p>Install dependencies, copy engine files, install migrations, and migrate database:</p>

<pre><code>bundle
rails lato_settings:install:application
rails lato_settings:install:migrations
rails db:migrate</code></pre>

<p>Mount engine in <code>config/routes.rb</code>:</p>

<pre><code>Rails.application.routes.draw do
  mount LatoSettings::Engine =&gt; "/lato-settings"

  # ...
end</code></pre>

<p>Import styles in <code>app/assets/stylesheets/application.scss</code>:</p>

<pre><code>@import "lato_settings/application";</code></pre>

<p>Import JavaScript in <code>app/javascript/application.js</code>:</p>

<pre><code>import "lato_settings/application"</code></pre>

<h3>Admin and permissions</h3>

<p>
  Engine pages require authenticated Lato session and admin permission.
  Access is allowed only to users with <code>lato_settings_admin</code> set to <code>true</code>.
</p>

<pre><code>user = Lato::User.find_by(email: "admin@example.com")
user.update!(lato_settings_admin: true)</code></pre>

<p>
  Engine root redirects to settings index, so mounted path becomes entry point for settings management UI.
</p>

<h3>Reading settings in application code</h3>

<p>
  Read values with <code>LatoSettings.get(key, default = nil)</code>.
  When key does not exist, method returns provided default value.
</p>

<pre><code>class ApplicationController &lt; Lato::ApplicationController
  def index
    @api_key = LatoSettings.get("api_key")
    @page_title = LatoSettings.get("page_title", "Default title")
    @items_per_page = LatoSettings.get("items_per_page", 25)
  end
end</code></pre>

<div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
  <h4 class="alert-heading">Deprecated API</h4>
  <p>
    Use <code>LatoSettings.get</code>. <code>LatoSettings::Setting.get</code> is deprecated and should not be used in new code.
  </p>
</div>

<h3>Creating initial settings</h3>

<p>
  Initial settings are usually created in <code>db/seeds.rb</code>.
  Recommended pattern is <code>find_or_create_by!</code> to avoid duplicates across repeated seed runs.
</p>

<pre><code>LatoSettings::Setting.find_or_create_by!(key: "site_name") do |setting|
  setting.value = "Lato Settings Example"
  setting.label = "Site name"
  setting.description = "The name of the site"
  setting.typology = :string
  setting.required = true
end</code></pre>

<p>
  Settings can also be created and updated directly from engine admin UI.
  New records first ask for typology, then show field type-specific form input.
</p>

<h3>Supported typologies</h3>

<div class="table-responsive">
  <table class="table table-striped align-middle">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Typology</th>
        <th>Stored value</th>
        <th>Returned by <code>LatoSettings.get</code></th>
        <th>Options support</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>string</code></td>
        <td>Text</td>
        <td><code>String</code></td>
        <td>No</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>number</code></td>
        <td>Numeric text</td>
        <td><code>Float</code></td>
        <td><code>min</code>, <code>max</code>, <code>step</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>date</code></td>
        <td>Date string</td>
        <td><code>Date</code></td>
        <td><code>min</code>, <code>max</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>select</code></td>
        <td>Selected option</td>
        <td><code>String</code> or <code>nil</code> if invalid</td>
        <td><code>values</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>integer</code></td>
        <td>Numeric text</td>
        <td><code>Integer</code></td>
        <td><code>min</code>, <code>max</code>, <code>step</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>text</code></td>
        <td>Long text</td>
        <td><code>String</code></td>
        <td>No</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h3>Options for advanced typologies</h3>

<p>
  Numeric, date, and select settings can define extra constraints in <code>options</code>.
</p>

<pre><code>LatoSettings::Setting.create!(
  key: "price_multiplier",
  value: 1.25,
  label: "Price multiplier",
  description: "Multiplier applied to base price",
  typology: :number,
  options: { min: 0, max: 10, step: 0.01 }
)

LatoSettings::Setting.create!(
  key: "launch_date",
  value: "2026-01-15",
  label: "Launch date",
  description: "Planned launch date",
  typology: :date,
  options: { min: "2026-01-01", max: "2026-12-31" }
)

LatoSettings::Setting.create!(
  key: "theme",
  value: "light",
  label: "Theme",
  description: "Active application theme",
  typology: :select,
  options: { values: ["light", "dark", "system"] }
)</code></pre>

<p>
  For <code>select</code>, stored value must exist in <code>options[:values]</code>. Otherwise formatted value becomes <code>nil</code>.
</p>

<h3>Validation and key normalization</h3>

<p>
  Setting keys must be unique and use only letters, numbers, and underscores.
  Before validation, key is normalized with lowercase and underscore formatting.
</p>

<pre><code>"Site Name"   # =&gt; "site_name"
"API-KEY"     # =&gt; "api_key"
"Main.Config" # =&gt; "main_config"</code></pre>

<p>
  Labels and values are required. Description is optional.
</p>

<h3>Required settings</h3>

<p>
  Set <code>required: true</code> when setting must exist in project and must not be deleted by admin users.
  Required settings are still editable, but destroy action is blocked.
</p>

<pre><code>LatoSettings::Setting.create!(
  key: "app_name",
  value: "My Application",
  label: "Application name",
  typology: :string,
  required: true
)</code></pre>

<h3>Cache behavior</h3>

<p>
  Values returned by <code>LatoSettings.get</code> are loaded from cache.
  Cache entry is stored in <code>Rails.cache</code> and expires after about one minute.
  Saving or destroying a setting resets cache immediately.
</p>

<pre><code>LatoSettings.reset_cache</code></pre>

<p>
  Manual reset is useful after low-level data changes outside normal model callbacks.
</p>
